# Unit Test Conventions

## Framework

- Use **Vitest** with `import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest"`
- Tests live in `lib/__tests__/` alongside the code they cover
- DOM-dependent tests use `// @vitest-environment happy-dom` at the top of the file

## Assertion Style

- Assert on whole objects with `toMatchObject` or `toEqual` unless specifically targeting an individual slice of a large object
- Avoid long chains of per-field `.toBe()` assertions when a single object assertion is clearer

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
expect(result.name).toBe(char.name);
expect(result.race).toBe(char.race);
expect(result.class).toBe(char.class);

// ✅ GOOD
expect(result).toMatchObject(char);
```

## Structure

- Group related tests under `describe` blocks by function or behavior
- Use clear, specific `it` descriptions that read as sentences
- Build test data with factory functions (e.g. `makeCharacter(overrides)`) to reduce boilerplate

## Prompting

- When adding or editing unit tests, **ask the user** if they want to add any new conventions to this rule file
